Novelis Inc. Key Developments

Novelis Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended March 31, 2017
May 10 17
Novelis Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of $2,621 million compared to $2,402 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was $88 million compared to $47 million a year ago. Net income attributable to the company’s common shareholder was $47 million compared to $29 million a year ago. EBITDA was $240 million compared to $215 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $292 million compared to $270 million a year ago.


For the year, the company reported net sales of $9,591 million compared to $9,872 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was $197 million compared to $8 million a year ago. Net income attributable to the company’s common shareholder was $45 million compared to loss of $38 million a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $575 million compared to $541 million a year ago. Capital expenditures were $224 million compared to $370 million a year ago. EBITDA was $840 million compared to $675 million a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $1,054 million compared to $791 million a year ago. Net Debt at March 31, 2017, was $4,852 million against $5,047 at March 31, 2016.


Novelis Inc. to Report Q4, 2017 Results on May 10, 2017
May 3 17
Novelis Inc. announced that they will report Q4, 2017 results at 9:00 AM, US Eastern Standard Time on May 10, 2017


Novelis Inc., Q4 2017 Earnings Call, May 10, 2017
May 3 17
Novelis Inc., Q4 2017 Earnings Call, May 10, 2017


